  <p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB;
  mso-no-proof:yes'>Freighters transport cargo between colonies, mining
  stations and space ports. They come in small, medium and large sizes.<o:p=
></o:p></span></p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB;
  mso-no-proof:yes'>Some freighter designs are shielded, but other designs =
choose
  to omit shields in favor of cost and speed</span>.<span lang=3DEN-GB
  style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB;mso-no-proof:yes'><o:p></o:p></span></p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB;
  mso-no-proof:yes'>Freighters work for your empire, but they are not yours.
  They belong to the private citizens in your empire. All transportation of
  goods in your empire is performed by private citizens.<o:p></o:p></span><=
/p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal><span lang=3DEN-GB style=3D'mso-ansi-language:EN-GB;
  mso-no-proof:yes'>Thus you cannot assign missions to Freighters.<o:p></o:=
p></span></p>
